Student Performance

Bootstrap Sample

Boot requires a custom function that would return row wise stats. In case of dataframe, each row is considered as a multi-variate observation. First parameter of the custom function takes the data input and second parameter takes the importance of data given current bootstrap iteration. stype defines second parameter.




#X <- as.data.frame(X)

#df.t <- get_sample_sizes(dim(X.p1)[1], dim(X.p1)[2])
df.t <- get_sample_sizes(dim(X.p1)[1] , dim(X.p1)[2]) #+ dim(X.p2)[1]

student_question_ratios <- df.t[[1]]
sample_sizes <- df.t[[2]]

df.t <- get_mean_sample_error(X.p1, X.p2, sample_sizes[1], student_question_ratios[1],2)
[1] "sample p1:94; sample p2:94"
[1] "Starting Boot 1"
[1] "Starting Boot 2"
df.error <- df.t[[1]]
df.error.agg <- df.t[[2]]


for(i in 2:length(sample_sizes)) {
  
  df.t <- get_mean_sample_error(X.p1, X.p2, sample_sizes[i], student_question_ratios[i],2)
  
  df.error.t <- df.t[[1]]
  df.error.agg.t <- df.t[[2]]

  df.error <- df.error %>% union(
    
    df.error.t
  )
  
  df.error.agg <- df.error.agg %>% union(
    
    df.error.agg.t
  )
  
}
